<HEADLINE>
6,000 RUNNERS TO COMPETE IN 2007 TAINAN INTERNATIONAL MARATHON
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tainan,  April 13 (CNA) 04/13/07  22:37:28 (By Han Nai-kuo)
</P>
<P>
The 2007 Tainan International Marathon will take place Sunday in
the city of Tainan, with 6,000 runners taking part, including 200
foreign athletes from 14 countries, Tainan Mayor Hsu Tien-tsai
said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Hsu told a press conference that the foreign runners are coming
from countries including the United States, Canada, the United
Kingdom, Germany, Greece, Portugal, Ireland, Hungary, Japan, the
Philippines and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He said the city government has invited world-class long-distance
runners to the race, including Bernard Mutai from Kenya, Oksana
K. Lokhlove from Russia, and China's medal-winning female
marathoner Hu Xiuying.
</P>
<P>
The race will start at 6 a.m. April 15 at the plaza in front of
the Tainan city government building. The event will be divided
into four categories: the 42.2-km marathon, the 21.1-km half
marathon, the 10-km race and the 3-km leisure run.
</P>
<P>
The route of the race allows runners to pass many historical and
cultural relics within the city, according to the mayor.
</P>
<P>
The first place winners in the men's and women's divisions of the
full marathon race will each receive a cash prize of NT$50,000.
Other prizes will be NT$30,000 for second place winners,
NT$20,000 for third place winners, NT$15,000 for fourth place
winners and NT$10,000 for fifth place winners.
</P>
<P>
Those placing first to fifth in the men's and women's divisions
of the half marathon race will also be entitled to cash prizes
ranging from NT$10,000 to NT$4,000.
</P>
